## Front Matter & Publication Details

**Bond Markets, Analysis, and Strategies** (Tenth Edition)
- Authors: **Frank J. Fabozzi** and **Francesco A. Fabozzi**
- Publisher: MIT Press (Cambridge, MA / London, England)
- Copyright: 2021 Massachusetts Institute of Technology
- ISBN: 9780262046275 (hardcover)
- Classification: Investment analysis, Portfolio management, Bond market

### Book Structure

32 chapters covering:
- Core pricing and yield concepts (Ch 1-4)
- Interest rate theory and term structure (Ch 5-6)
- Securities: Treasury, agency, corporate, municipal, international, mortgages (Ch 7-17)
- Trading and liquidity (Ch 18)
- Embedded options analysis (Ch 19-21)
- Credit analysis and modeling (Ch 22-23)
- Portfolio management strategies and construction (Ch 24-28)
- Derivatives: futures, options, swaps, credit default swaps (Ch 29-32)

## Preface

### Book Evolution and Objectives

- **First edition (1989)**: Covered products, analytical techniques for valuing bonds, quantifying interest rate exposure, portfolio strategies
- **Tenth edition (2021)**: Substantially updated all areas with practical applications from third-party commercial vendors
- Benefited from feedback: readers, instructors at universities/training programs, chief investment officers, portfolio managers, analysts, traders, regulators
- Tradition continues: providing up-to-date bond market information and portfolio management tools

### Changes from Ninth Edition

**Removed chapters:**
- Former Ch 17 ("Interest Rate Models") and Ch 21 ("Measuring Credit Spread Exposures of Corporate Bonds") removed based on instructor feedback (too technical)
- Ch 17 still available on MIT Press website: https://mitpress.mit.edu/bond-markets-tenth-edition
- Former Ch 21 split between Ch 4 ("Bond Price Volatility") and new Ch 26 ("Managing a Corporate Bond Portfolio")

**New chapters:**
- **Ch 5**: "The Theory and History of Interest Rates"
  - Describes different theories about interest rate level determination
  - Addresses **safe asset controversy** (existence of a safe/riskless asset)
  - Covers **negative interest rates**
- **Ch 18**: "Liquidity and Trading of Credit/Spread Products"
  - Trading bonds is more challenging than equity markets
  - Covers trade processing and critical third-party vendor services

**Completely revised chapters:**
- **Ch 10**: "International Bonds" (now includes appendix on foreign-exchange rates)
- **Ch 26**: "Managing a Corporate Bond Portfolio"
  - Explains how bond portfolio managers use **style factors** (regularly used in equity management)

**New appendix:**
- **Investment Management Agreement**: Legal document setting forth service terms when bond portfolio management company provides services to individual/organization

### Instructor Supplements

**Electronic Instructor's Manual with Solutions:**
- Prepared by Dr. Rob Hull (Washburn University School of Business)
- Contains chapter summaries and suggested answers to all end-of-chapter questions
- Available to instructors at https://mitpress.mit.edu/bond-markets-tenth-edition

**PowerPoint Presentation:**
- Prepared by Dr. Rob Hull
- Individual lecture outlines accompanying text
- Includes all figures and tables from text
- Lecture notes modifiable to reflect specific presentation needs
- Available to instructors at https://mitpress.mit.edu/bond-markets-tenth-edition

